<i>Me, too.</i>

728
01:04:34,104 --> 01:04:36,771
Such a precious gift.

729
01:04:36,773 --> 01:04:39,608
So, hurting little Julian

730
01:04:41,510 --> 01:04:43,879
it's not going
to be easy for me.

731
01:04:43,881 --> 01:04:45,480
[Crying]

732
01:04:45,482 --> 01:04:47,015
He's so smooth.

733
01:04:50,653 --> 01:04:52,988
<i>What's your plan, Tommy?</i>

734
01:04:55,424 --> 01:04:56,691
What's your plan, Tommy?

735
01:05:02,531 --> 01:05:06,868
<i>We can't go out.</i>
<i>After the park, the police</i>
<i>are looking for us, too.</i>

736
01:05:13,042 --> 01:05:17,379
We're hiding out
in an old house
in west London.

737
01:05:17,381 --> 01:05:19,347
<i>I'll text you
the address</i>

738
01:05:20,950 --> 01:05:22,984
<i>and you come meet us here.</i>

739
01:05:24,353 --> 01:05:25,754
Okay?

740
01:05:28,024 --> 01:05:29,391
No more tricks.

741
01:05:33,696 --> 01:05:35,630
Keep fucking quiet.

742
01:05:38,000 --> 01:05:40,035
[Tires screeching]

743
01:05:57,286 --> 01:05:59,054
Better text Khan.

744
01:06:01,157 --> 01:06:02,824
Yeah.

745
01:06:04,660 --> 01:06:07,095
You really think
he's going to come?

746
01:06:07,097 --> 01:06:09,798
<i>Yeah.</i>

747
01:06:09,800 --> 01:06:12,534
It's all about honor
with that guy.

748
01:06:16,038 --> 01:06:17,706
Sent.

749
01:06:21,077 --> 01:06:23,645
You know they're going
to have guns, right?

750
01:06:28,117 --> 01:06:30,185
Guns are for pussies.

751
01:06:39,428 --> 01:06:41,129
[Beeping]

752
01:07:08,691 --> 01:07:11,126
<i>[Cell phone ringing]</i>

753
01:07:13,429 --> 01:07:15,597
Yeah.

754
01:07:15,599 --> 01:07:17,499
(Jack)
Look who's come
for dinner.

755
01:07:18,968 --> 01:07:21,136
Anna?

756
01:07:23,172 --> 01:07:24,773
Get ready.

757
01:07:30,312 --> 01:07:33,248
This is the perfect place.

758
01:07:33,250 --> 01:07:35,016
For what?

759
01:07:53,636 --> 01:07:55,804
<i>I see no cash.</i>

760
01:07:55,806 --> 01:07:59,340
It's in the house.
Safe.

761
01:07:59,342 --> 01:08:01,109
Don't fuck with me.

762
01:08:01,111 --> 01:08:03,311
<i>Jack, you can have the money</i>

763
01:08:03,313 --> 01:08:06,681
just as soon
as we get Sarah
and Julian.

764
01:08:17,359 --> 01:08:18,660
<i>Where's Mrs. Tommy?</i>

765
01:08:18,662 --> 01:08:21,930
She's inside,
with the money.

766
01:08:38,447 --> 01:08:40,048
What the fuck.

767
01:08:40,050 --> 01:08:42,650
Honey, I'm home.

768
01:08:49,992 --> 01:08:51,226
Mrs. Tommy.

769
01:08:51,228 --> 01:08:53,128
[Cocks gun]

770
01:08:55,831 --> 01:08:59,000
<i>You got five seconds</i>
<i>to show me the money</i>
<i>or I'm shooting your husband.</i>

771
01:08:59,002 --> 01:09:01,503
<i>(Anna)
The money's up here.</i>

772
01:09:01,505 --> 01:09:03,738
How can I be sure?

773
01:09:09,178 --> 01:09:12,280
<i>I just want Sarah,
I want Julian,</i>

774
01:09:12,282 --> 01:09:15,150
<i>but if you hurt them
or my husband,</i>

775
01:09:15,152 --> 01:09:17,852
<i>I will destroy
all of it.</i>

776
01:09:17,854 --> 01:09:21,089
That's impressive.
I'll get them over.

777
01:09:24,126 --> 01:09:25,860
[Whistles]

778
01:09:32,434 --> 01:09:33,835
<i>Get the fuck out, love.</i>

779
01:09:38,340 --> 01:09:40,041
Now it's your turn.

780
01:10:00,229 --> 01:10:02,497
Well done, sweetheart.

781
01:10:02,499 --> 01:10:04,165
Now the bag.

782
01:10:23,219 --> 01:10:24,219
Jack?

783
01:10:36,298 --> 01:10:38,433
Are you all right?

784
01:10:40,603 --> 01:10:41,903
[Weak chuckle]

785
01:10:41,905 --> 01:10:43,805
<i>[Nailing]</i>

786
01:10:47,142 --> 01:10:48,309
Sarah!

787
01:10:52,548 --> 01:10:53,915
<i>(Anna)
Sarah!</i>

788
01:10:53,917 --> 01:10:56,351
<i>[Gunshots]</i>

789
01:11:06,895 --> 01:11:09,764
Go out the ladder.

790
01:11:09,766 --> 01:11:12,233
<i>[Whispering]</i>
<i>Sarah, go out</i>
<i>the ladder.</i>

791
01:11:12,235 --> 01:11:13,868
[Muffled grunt]

792
01:12:25,941 --> 01:12:28,443
Oh, God.
Give me Julian.
Give me Julian

793
01:13:07,816 --> 01:13:09,350
[chuckles]

794
01:13:18,727 --> 01:13:20,862
[Grunts]

795
01:13:31,106 --> 01:13:33,141
<i>[Julian crying]</i>

796
01:13:37,613 --> 01:13:40,381
<i>[Jet flies by]</i>

797
01:13:52,661 --> 01:13:54,128
[Beeping]

798
01:14:30,732 --> 01:14:32,433
<i>[Jet flies by]</i>

799
01:14:49,918 --> 01:14:51,452
<i>[Sarah screams]</i>

800
01:15:21,183 --> 01:15:24,185
<i>[Boards creak]</i>

801
01:15:59,988 --> 01:16:01,255
Andre?

802
01:17:08,090 --> 01:17:10,458
<i>[Boards creak]</i>

803
01:17:43,225 --> 01:17:45,660
<i>(Khan)</i>
<i>You betrayed me,</i>
<i>Mr. Wright.</i>

804
01:17:47,229 --> 01:17:49,964
<i>You cannot undo that.</i>

805
01:17:49,966 --> 01:17:52,867
You must be sacrificed
<i>pour le bien de tous.</i>

806
01:17:56,338 --> 01:17:58,806
<i>[Nail gun fires]</i>

807
01:17:58,808 --> 01:18:00,675
<i>The greater good.</i>

808
01:18:01,743 --> 01:18:04,245
[Gunshots]

809
01:18:25,734 --> 01:18:27,735
Does not seem fair.

810
01:18:27,737 --> 01:18:31,706
You are playing with toys
while I am not playing
at all.

811
01:19:06,541 --> 01:19:09,310
You are a worthy adversary.

812
01:19:10,879 --> 01:19:12,446
<i>[Gunshot]</i>

813
01:19:18,920 --> 01:19:20,354
Ahh!

814
01:19:27,696 --> 01:19:28,829
Anna.

815
01:19:32,033 --> 01:19:33,234
<i>Anna.</i>

816
01:19:35,170 --> 01:19:36,971
[Gasping]

817
01:19:43,445 --> 01:19:44,779
<i>Anna.</i>

818
01:19:51,419 --> 01:19:53,587
<i>[Gunshot]</i>

819
01:20:22,150 --> 01:20:25,319
<i>[Lady newscaster]</i>
<i>Metro police today</i>
<i>announced a breakthrough</i>

820
01:20:25,321 --> 01:20:29,824
<i>in a case that's traumatized</i>
<i>people living in the sleepy</i>
<i>London suburb of mortlake.</i>

821
01:20:29,826 --> 01:20:34,328
<i>It comes just 36 hours</i>
<i>after a shootout which left</i>
<i>five people dead</i>

822
01:20:34,330 --> 01:20:39,667
<i>a house burnt to the ground,</i>
<i>and the entire community</i>
<i>in shock.</i>

823
01:20:39,669 --> 01:20:41,735
<i>With me is superintendent
ray Martin,</i>

824
01:20:41,737 --> 01:20:43,537
<i>one of the officers
in charge of the case.</i>

825
01:20:43,539 --> 01:20:45,840
<i>Superintendent,
what can you tell us?</i>

826
01:20:45,842 --> 01:20:48,175
<i>We can now confirm
that these tragic events</i>

827
01:20:48,177 --> 01:20:51,078
<i>are directly linked
to a drug turf war</i>

828
01:20:51,080 --> 01:20:55,716
<i>which began with an armed</i>
<i>robbery that turned deadly</i>
<i>in an east end night club</i>.

829
01:20:55,718 --> 01:20:58,419
<i>(Halden)</i>
<i>Remarkable.</i>
Hi.

830
01:20:58,421 --> 01:21:03,424
<i>...and extraordinary bravery</i>
<i>of veteran detective</i>
<i>John halden</i>

831
01:21:03,426 --> 01:21:06,861
<i>a man I consider to be</i>
<i>a personal friend</i>
<i>and a colleague.</i>

832
01:21:06,863 --> 01:21:09,964
It's easy to be a hero
when you're writing
your own story.

833
01:21:13,034 --> 01:21:16,737
Uh, the firemen found this.

834
01:21:16,739 --> 01:21:17,938
It's, um...

835
01:21:19,541 --> 01:21:22,843
it's not much,
but, uh, it's yours.

836
01:21:32,754 --> 01:21:34,421
Good luck.

837
01:21:40,028 --> 01:21:42,329
<i>[Muffled voices]</i>

838
01:21:42,331 --> 01:21:44,031
Hm.

839
01:21:55,577 --> 01:21:57,211
(Tom)
What took you so long?

840
01:21:57,213 --> 01:21:59,513
I just had to do one last thing.

841
01:21:59,515 --> 01:22:02,483
All right.
Say goodbye
to this hell hole.

842
01:22:05,387 --> 01:22:06,854
Come on.

843
01:22:19,234 --> 01:22:22,002
So, no more Sushi nights.

844
01:22:42,123 --> 01:22:45,693
<i>[Serena ryder
singing "for you"]</i>

